data.comment: The match has started.
Free kick for Tokyo in the half of Nagoya.

Leandro for Tokyo is whistled offside.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Tokyo.

Free kick Tokyo.

Free kick for Tokyo in their own half.
Nagoya awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 15, Yusuke Araki signals a free kick to Nagoya.
Nagoya have a dangerous throw-in.
Ball safe as Tokyo is awarded a throw-in in their half.

In Tokyo a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Yusuke Araki signals a free kick to Nagoya.

A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Yusuke Araki awards the home team a throw-in.

Goal! Leandro gives Tokyo a 1-0 lead in Tokyo.
That's a fine assist from Kensuke Nagai.

Kensuke Nagai gets his shot on target but fails to score for Tokyo.
Throw-in for Tokyo at Ajinomoto Stadium.

2 minutes of injury time will be added to the 1st half.
In Tokyo Tokyo attack through Yojiro Takahagi. The finish is off target, however.

Tokyo's Leandro gets in a shot but it is blocked by a Nagoya defender.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Tokyo.
In the minute 45, The first-half has ended.

Free kick for Tokyo in the half of Nagoya.
Nagoya make their second substitution with Yuki Soma replacing Naoki Maeda.

Nagoya needs to be cautious. Tokyo have an attacking throw-in.
In the minute 48, Free kick for Tokyo in their own half.
Free kick Tokyo.
Can Nagoya capitalize from this dangerous free kick?
In the minute 51, Nagoya's Mateus is on target but unsuccessful.
Goal kick for Tokyo at Ajinomoto Stadium.
Throw-in for Tokyo in their own half.

Throw-in for Tokyo close to the penalty box.

Can Nagoya get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Tokyo's half?

Throw-in for Nagoya in the half of Tokyo.

Throw-in for Tokyo in the half of Nagoya.
Nagoya awarded a free kick in their own half.

Nagoya to take a throw-in in Tokyo territory.
Corner awarded to Nagoya.

Yusuke Araki signals a free kick to Nagoya.
The away team replace Joao Schmidt with Ryotaro Ishida.
In the minute 68, Nagoya are whistled for offside.
Adailton is replacing Kensuke Nagai for the home team.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
In the minute 70, Can Tokyo get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Nagoya's half?
Free kick for Nagoya in their own half.

Throw-in for Tokyo in their own half.

Tokyo awarded a free kick in their own half.

Throw-in for Nagoya at Ajinomoto Stadium.

Penalty! Yusuke Araki points to the spot, great chance for Tokyo...
A massive blow for Tokyo as Adailton misses from the spot.
It's 1-0 as the referee blows for full-time.
Hirotaka Mita is on a sub for Shuto Abe for Tokyo.
Tokyo make their fourth substitution with Taichi Hara replacing Leandro.
Mitch Langerak for Nagoya has been booked by Yusuke Araki and receives a first yellow card.
